Chairperson for The Judicial Commission of Inquiry into Allegations of State Capture, Raymond Zondo. AFP/Guillem Sartorio JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry is seeking another extension. The State Capture Inquiry is seeking another extension. Commission Chair, Justice Raymond Zondo, has applied for a 3-month extension to complete its work. Courtesy #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/dnoYkjmwmy Commission Chair, Justice Raymond Zondo, has applied for a 3-month extension to complete its work. READ: Makhosi Khoza testifies at state capture inquiry The commission has cited the lockdown among other things that have delayed it. Zondo wants the High Court in Pretoria to allow the commission to continue until the end of June. Among some outstanding testimonies is that of Former President Jacob Zuma who is refusing to appear.